diketopiperazine Trp-Arg present in the deep-sea sponge Geodia barretti
A quinolone that is quinolin-4(1H)-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 5, and 8. It is isolated from the sponge Aplysina aerophoba.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-(5-hydroxyindol-3-yl)pyruvic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major species at pH 7.3.
A dipeptide zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of Ala-Ala; major species at pH 7.3.
